Member # 16592
<P>

</FONT>
</TD>
<TD>
<IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/icons/icon14.gif" BORDER="0" ALIGN="ABSCENTER">
<FONT SIZE="1" color="#000000" face="Verdana, Arial">
posted July 26, 2001 04:05 PM &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
<A HREF="http://forums.castersrealm.com/cgi-bin/eq/ultimatebb.cgi?ubb=get_profile&u=00016592" target=_blank>
<IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/profile.gif" BORDER="0" ALT="Profile for The O"></A> &nbsp;&nbsp;<A HREF="http://" target=_new><IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/homepage.gif" BORDER="0" ALT="Author's Homepage"></A> &nbsp;  &nbsp;&nbsp;<A HREF="http://forums.castersrealm.com/cgi-bin/eq/ultimatebb.cgi?ubb=edit_post&f=295&t=000070&reply_num=000000&u=00016592"><IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/edit_ubb6.gif" BORDER="0" ALT="Edit/Delete Post"></A> &nbsp;&nbsp;<A HREF="http://forums.castersrealm.com/cgi-bin/eq/ultimatebb.cgi?ubb=reply&f=295&t=000070&replyto=000000"><IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/quote_ubb6.gif" BORDER="0" ALT="Reply With Quote"></A>
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I need to throw my lot in with the multitudes of disgruntled Magicians out there.  I have been playing my Mage from back in the day when there was no Kunark, no going past 50 and no epics.  I like to think I'm pretty old-school and have an idea of what game balance is. Since it's been apart of my entertainment lifestyle for about 2 years.  I feel at times that the people designing spells and items for our game do not actually play it themselves.  Not to sound too critical, in thier place I would completely understand. You spend 8 or more hours a day crunching numbers, coming up with names and challenges, then dealing with customer complaints regarding your work. It's doubtful you'd choose to do the same thing for fun. I want to continue to play and be excited about not only my class but it's place in the game that I enjoy so much.  What I'm seeing in the Luclin spell list is not game balance.  It simply is not.  I think everyone that has put substantial time into this class will agree.  Example: Druids can already port, buff, heal have stackable DoT's that add up to more damage than our blasts and are now being handed a spell that simply out-guns us too.  The designer argument there is that our pets are the main focus of our damage and abilities.  I understand that. I'm all for it. That's what I love most about my magician.  However I do not have the tools to make that theory a reality in the tough high level challenges out there.  The cleric in my group has the option of healing my pet, or the player controlled tank.  I can not fault the decision when my pet is defeated but the warrior battles on.  However where does that leave me?  Nuke?  Most of mine take too long and will draw attention to myself that I have no way of evading without a pet.  Evac?  Well I can gate out, but what will that do for the others?  Summon a new pet?  Not likely in the middle of a tight fight, if I haven't got time to nuke then I haven't got time to summon.  Burn my mana for mod rods so that the casters with options can use them?  I find myself in that inferior position alot.  I am presenting ideas for spells that I think are not only well within game balance, but will also have alot of player magicians excited and in agreement.  I hope this post is seen by the designers who will no doubt take this plea under advisement. <P>Summon Phantom Leather lvl 20- See summon Phantom Plate<P>Summon Mask of the Magician lvl 24- Summon No Rent Mask AC 1 Face or main slot, with random Racial Illusion.<P>Firetree's Familiar Augment lvl 29-  Sounds great!  More pet buffs would be very cool.  I am however concerned that this spell is not intended for OUR pets but instead meant to be used to enhance these new "familiars".  That would be an insult to our class.  Not only give our main ability of pets to other classes, but then give us a spell only designed to increase the power of that insult.<P>Summon Phantom Chain lvl 29- See Summon Phantom Plate<P>Summon Trickster's Boots lvl 29- Summon No Rent boots AC 4 feet or main slots that have two charges of Shadow Step<P>Summon Cloak of Cloak of Shadows lvl 34- Summon No Rent Cloak AC 5 back and main slots that has two charges of Invisibility<P>Summon Phantom Plate lvl 39-  If this spell series is usable by our pets, significantly increasing thier AC and possibly hit points, I'm all for it.  We do not need another useless trinket to offer fighters in wipeout scenerios.  I would rather be able to prevent the group from being eliminated rather than having little to offer when it is.<P>Enhance Summoning lvl 39- a 400 hp heal to pet<P>Summon Mana Shard lvl 44- Summons a No Drop mana shard, effect: Harvest.  Casting time 4 seconds.  Casting time when clicked for effect, 10 seconds.  Mana Cost 10. Recast time 10 minutes.  Mana gained 171-301.<P>Revitalize Summoning lvl 49- Heal over time to pet 600 hp.<P>Summon Elemental Blanket lvl 49-  mmmm.. warm!<P>Walnan's Familiar Augment lvl 49- An improved version of the level 29 SoL spell.<P>Summon Tourniquet lvl 52-  I gotta admit as someone that still gets alot of use out of thier bind wounds skill I'm pretty pleased about this one.  I have to wonder though if I stand in a minority.<P>Bristlebane's Bag of Tricks lvl 53- Summons a glowing back pack with a Ring of Flight, a Modulating Rod, Magician's Mask, Cloak of Shadows and Trickster's Boots<P>Veil of the Elements lvl 54-  Not bad, would be better if it were sharable, making the magician class more group friendly.<P>Summon Rod of Mystical Transvergence lvl 56-  If this spell is in fact an improved Mod Rod that will actually increase my mana pool rather than eating away at my life and mana for no results, then I'm all for it.<P>Revitalize Summoning lvl 57- an 800 hit point heal over time to pet.<P>Cyclone lvl 57- an AoE radiating from the magician that deals 225 and carries a 4 to 8 second stun.<P>Raging Elements lvl 57- Summons a random elemental equal to the level 39 Lesser Conjuration series of pets.  Casting time 2.5 seconds.<P>Lava Pit lvl 58- A fire based Root 600 hp DoT<BR>(if wizards can get "familiars" we are entitled to finally get a root spell<P>Transon's Terrible Torment lvl 58- Hats off to you guys!  Can't wait to scribe this one!<P>Shield of the Arch Magi lvl 59-  A greater Shield Spell with HP , AC, Magic Resist like the previous ones in this series with the added ability of Fire and Cold resists added to make it more Magician Specific.  Much like Shield of the Magi and Elemental Armor combined and improved.  I think this spell should be shared by wizards. Necromancers should have increased poison and disease resist added to thiers rather than fire and cold, while the Enchanter version has more magic resist than the others but lesser resist bonuses to fire, cold, poison and disease added on it.<P>Summon Fires of Solusek Ro lvl 59-  Summons a No Rent, No Drop fire crystal effect Manaskin.  Mana cost 400.  casting time when cast and clicked for effect 5 seconds.  Max duration 2 hours.Spell Component 1 peridot.  Self Protective skin 400.  Self Mana regen (1).<P>Anti-Summoning Shield lvl 60-  I'm actually very excited about this spell, however another fellow magician raised a very interesting point.  Wouldn't this spell actually cause more problems than it would cure?  The way aggro works if the monster can not summon the offending player from a distance, isn't it likely to decide to pursue that player?  Making the job of the fighters to contain and beat down the beast more difficult because now they must chase it?<P>Burnout V lvl 60-  I'd like to see a substantial improvement over Burnout IV.  Which is a good spell but feels like an intermediary to something better to come.<P>Failure of Magi'Kot lvl 60- Summons a random elemental slightly more powerful than a greater voceration of it's randomed type.  However it can not be controlled by the magician.  It will act and react like an enchanter animation.  Casting time 5 seconds.<P>Strength of Brell Serillis lvl 60- 1000 heal over time to pet.<P>Touch of the Elemental Master lvl 60- Magic based direct damage spell.  Mana 375.  Casting time 6 seconds.  Recast time 4 seconds.  Yield 1115 damage.  (I'm sorry Druids of all classes being able to out nuke the magician on top of all thier other can-do's IS NOT game balance.)<P>  <IMG SRC="cool.gif" border="0">
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
