<IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/profile.gif" BORDER="0" ALT="Profile for Pharmag"></A> &nbsp;&nbsp;<A HREF="http://" target=_new><IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/homepage.gif" BORDER="0" ALT="Author's Homepage"></A> &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<A HREF="http://forums.castersrealm.com/cgi-bin/eq/ultimatebb.cgi?ubb=private_message&u=00007663"><IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/priv_message.gif" BORDER='0' ALT="Send New Private Message"></A> &nbsp;&nbsp;<A HREF="http://forums.castersrealm.com/cgi-bin/eq/ultimatebb.cgi?ubb=edit_post&f=295&t=000070&reply_num=000001&u=00007663"><IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/edit_ubb6.gif" BORDER="0" ALT="Edit/Delete Post"></A> &nbsp;&nbsp;<A HREF="http://forums.castersrealm.com/cgi-bin/eq/ultimatebb.cgi?ubb=reply&f=295&t=000070&replyto=000001"><IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/quote_ubb6.gif" BORDER="0" ALT="Reply With Quote"></A>
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
It's actually nice for once to see someone who really has played a magician post. I too often find I am basically useless when a train comes through, always I will kill my pet so that it doesn't get in the way, rather then trying to control it.. The risk isn't worth the damage reward. Was really annoyed at the CoH nerf, since I use to use that spell to clear enchanter aggro after they mezzed a train. Hate when something is nerfed without any consideration for the class, just to fix a end game exploit of it. They always opt to nerf the tools, rather then fix the exploits.<P>I just hate zoning into a place like Sebilis to find someone has trained something to zone in, and its on me when I've loaded in. Magician is the only class at 60 I can think of who is guaranteed dead when this happens. 10sec pets, 5sec gate are the only options. This is the same kindof helplessness we have when pet dies solo or when highly aggro in a group. I just don't agree that we are so much more powerful then a wizard, that we deserve the negatives of no defense. Before Kunark, and the balancing I would have, but not now.<P>I don't really have much in the way of good ideas on how to fix the class, I'm not a big fan of summonings, since nothing sofar has been even close to the spell version of what they try to clone.. I'm of the opinion summoned items due to the casting time + trading should be better then the spells in some way.<P>I would just like to see our damage be weighted in consideration of the negatives, not just what other classes have in the same spell area. Wizards, Druids, Necros, Shamans, and alot of meleers out damage magicians, without the huge disadvantage of zero defense. We really need less resists. Both manastorm and Sirocco are sitting on about 40% chance to outright resist per wave. And their average damage per cast is less 1/3 of their potential damage. Making them the worst newks in the game save none.<P>I also feel that the magicians are being balanced around the epic pet, with the assumption every single magician has it, or will get it easily. That just isn't the case, infact is the epic which has been completed the least. I also don't like how its the only epic which costs mana, and has the longest casting time of any epic.<P>Honestly, I feel the magician loses alot to the misconception chainsummoning provides. People see magicians taking down things they can just pull off in a few seconds flat, or camping low level spawns easily. This does allow magicians to camp low level stuff easily, but any class can do that. Sadly, if they were really interested in fixing the magician class, they would have to completely break it first to remove the stimga. To do this they would have to do nothing more then make /pet get lost unusable while casting and the class is hopelessly broken. Then they could set about balancing it..<P>--------------------<P>58th Blackguard <BR>60th Arch CoH (retired)<P>"Rogues rule, Magicians suck, any questions?"
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
