<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I have to agree.  As a mage goes up in lvls his ability to solo decreases and so does his ability to find a group.  I do wonder though whether that is because of the spells we get or because people really don't know what a mage can and can't do.  Now on the negative side pets a rea problem in dungeon areas and regardless of what Verant says it is still not fixed enough.  Also our pet buffs and heals are really weak.  I mean on a earth pet at lvl 44 that has some where around 1500 hp that little 200hp buff is nothing.  Why can't mages have a pet complete healing spell at say lvl 49?  At least then when we can't find a group we could keep our pet alive longer.  Next thing is why don't mages get some sort of root, snare or fear.  Every other spell casting class has this ability in one form or another.  Necro's get a darkness line and they have a pet, shammies have root and they get a pet, druids have snare and they get a pet-ie a pathetic one for the spell lvl but never the less a pet.  Enchanters have pets and they get stuns, and roots.  Mages are the only class with no means of escape should our pet die. So in the all new spell list why not give mages some sort of root, snare or fear?  I mean I like the dot's, they are great but I mean I always thought dots were the realm of the necros, shammies and druids.  I would be glad to give up the dot's for some effective escape means if my pet dies.  <P>Now on the other point-it is still funny even at lvl 44 and fighting in the dreadlands how many people are amazed at teh amount of damage that my pets can do.  In a group it is like having another tank.  I wish more people would give mages a chance.  Between my pet, a few well placed nukes, and having the best damge shields in the game mages are very group friendly.  And speaking of damage shields-why do the mages never get a group damage shield?  <P>It is small stuff like this that could make mages extremely attractive to groups even at the higher end game.  Add these to call of the hero, and the new antisummoning spell and no raid would be complete without us.  Just my 2cp worth.<P>Wildayen-lvl 51 Wanderer<BR>Yalmatik-lvl 44 Mage
</FONT>
