BT, <P>I have to disagree with some of the facts you said about druids. Druids are not necessary the second best soloers. I have seen some mages and wizards solo better than a druid at higher levels. Heck I seen shaman out solo druids at higher levels. As for group wise druids do not usually have any trouble finding groups. The are far from being at the bottom of the group list. Druids can heal, snare, cast damage shields, nuke, evac, and buff. Many things that makes a class welcome in a group. Now I agree with what you had to say about necro's. They are the best soloers in the game and are on the bottom of the list for a group. That don't offer much to groups other than a mana battery. Also they have some debuffs, but other classes out shine them in groups. <P>Now I do agree wilias that elemental mastery should have the mana cost raised and the damage raise to 1150 to equal about the same as druids. Pet wise I think the mage class is good with what they have other than I want to see our 50+ air pet become a monk instead of a warrior. The air pet fits better as a monk with it's higher agility and stealthyness. That way magician after level 50 will have a warrior, wizard, rogue and monk pets, instead of 2 warriors, a rogue, and a wizard. As for the summoning items I think those items will be useful because we can give them to our pets.<BR>Well that my 2 cp worth.
