<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Oh hot topic!   <IMG SRC="biggrin.gif" border="0"> I would however like to keep the main focus of this thread on magicians.  If I may sum up the feelings I'm getting from many of the magicians out there responding. <P>Every magician seems to be in agreement that druids should not be getting a stronger nuke than us.<P>We all seem to think that pet heals are called for.  Especially since the designer claim is that the main focus of our abilities is within our pets.<P>Also on that note many magicians feel that the argument that we do not need snare/root/shadowstep because of our pets is now invalid because the designers have given pets to classes with those abilites.  Wizards, Druids and Necromancers.  Whether or not the Wizard and Druid pets are capable defenders of thier masters is beside the point that the designers themselves have set.<P>I think it can safely be said that if we must be the summoners of crap.  Then it should be crap that has uses in the mid level game at the very least.  No warrior type out there is really interested in the mage summoned armor.  Even if they were, speaking as someone that has lead raids and difficult corpse retrievals.  I can't imagine wasting the time to outfit the fighters with gear they don't really care about anyway.  And as I've said before, I'd rather have more to offer to prevent my group from being eliminated rather than little to offer when it is.<P>Lastly as a class we need some form of escape.  Whether it be in a pet that can be summoned quickly so that we can run, or in some form of invulnerability similiar to our necromancer cousins is debatable.  I think the fast pet would be more class specific, but there are those that disagree and feel we are not treated fairly there.  The argument is sound.<P>Opinions?  Comments?  What say you?
