<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I think the issue of who has the stronger nuke is somewhat moot at this point since the MOBs we're fighting at Level 60 are resisting a large percentage of the nukes anyway - Maloed or not.<P>The main focus, as far as I'm concerned, is the pets.  We're told time and time again that we're a pet-based class, and yet the pets are so mistrusted and reviled at our level that it's very rare that I'm permitted to have one.  And, with this in mind, it's something of an insult to present us with a pet as the result of our Epic quest.  You can argue the fact that we now have better control of our pets with people until you're blue in the face.  The fact remains that people no longer trust us with our pets - our best weapon.  In order to return our class to being a viable 'raiding' class, something has to be done to demonstrate to the people who lead raids that we now have control of our pets.  I have no suggestions to this end.  I just feel that this is what is killing our class and forcing us to solo our way through our 'golden years'.<P>I'm fully behind you that we've become 'summoners of crap'.  The biggest slap in the face was probably 'Bristlebane's Bundle'.  My sense of humor is as good as anyone's, but give us some things that are purposeful before you start endowing us with 'fun stuff'.  If you want us to be 'summoners' give us something useful to summon once we get to the higher levels.  Even Shard of the Core is somewhat embarrassing considering the anemic stats it provides.  And they still haven't given us a decent weapon to summon for our pets.  Two and a half years after the game launch and the pet of the 'master summoner' still fights as well barehanded as he does with our 'summoned items'!<P>As far as getting root and snare and better escape options, I'm not sure I agree.  If you're looking to root, cast an earth pet.  If you want to stun, get an air pet.  If you're looking for a means of escape, just keep your eye on your pet's health.  People argue back and forth on it, but if you're soloing, the only option as far as I'm concerned is the earth pet combined with Malosi.  If the MOB's Malosied, Root will stay long enough for you to either cast another pet or gate.  That's our version of an escape option.<P>In summation - fix our pets and you fix us.
</FONT>
