<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
&gt;The fact remains that people no longer trust us with our pets - our best weapon. In order to return our class to being a viable 'raiding' class, something has to be done to demonstrate to the people who lead raids that we now have control of our pets.<P>It's not really an issue whether we are trusted with our pets or not. I don't care how good a magician thinks they are, a pet is useless against alot of endgame fights. Pets have almost no resisting ability, and as a result go down in about the second or third wave of area .. so they do around 200-400dmg per pet. They cost 400mana to summon, so thats less then 1 to 1, making them unefficient. <P>Fear is another huge problem. We do get an immunity to fear spell, but that is easily dispelled, and when it does, you can't reapply due to the recast time.<P>The worst problem of all is the level at which a pet considers. Their lower level means they have a higher aggro range, and will train things that simply won't to an all 60 raiding group.<P>The focus later on for magicians really needs to be taken away from the pets, and concentrated more on damage output. I don't think magicians should be useless alot of the time endgame, like they currently are, outside CoH and Mod Rods. I would like to see spells added to the class which will make them a very valuable class to have on raids, useful in numbers, and perhaps 100% needed for some raids like warriors and clerics are needed for all. Here is 3 suggestions just along the lines of what I mean:<P>1. level 60 dmg shield: Instead of being the utterly useless 1/100th damage back that is taken, that the 56th one is. Make it a short duration 8-12secs damage shield which does like 200+ damage per hit. Add a recast time, and every raid would love to have a few magicians along.<P>2. A phantom shielding BUFF, which absorbs a fixed amount of damage. So if you get hit normally for 500, you get hit for say 450s.<P>3. Summoning pets which hit for uber melee damage, but proc a self damaging direct damage each hit, so they only last for a fixed duration. 400dmg, takes 50dmg, has 300hp. Something like that.<BR>-<P>Yes, I have to agree also that ALL summoned items magicians get are a joke. Most of the stuff is inferior to easily obtained items in the game, class specific, or humor spells. <P>No other class in the game gets abilities/spells post 50 which are 100% purely once off novelty items, with no use in grouping, raiding or trading. If we have to get these spells, they should be in addition to the functional spells count that other classes get.<BR>-<P>Newks are shocking. There are only a few exceptions to 60+ encounters which don't outright resist magician direct damage. Perhaps we shouldn't be the best or even second best damage in one cast, but we shouldn't have the worst resists of all classes either.<P>--------------------<P>58th Blackguard <BR>60th Arch CoH (retired)<P>"Rogues rule, Magicians suck, any questions?"
