<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
While I agree with your comments about pets in an 'Endgame' encounter, I really feel the need to emphasize their usefulness in those pre-Lvl. 60 situations.  I think the VAST majority of folks who are going to be affected by the Luclin spells are far from level 60 and so DO have a genuine concern about how the magician's pet is viewed by the people who put together raids.  Until folks come to understand that many of the pathing problems in the Planes have been resolved by patches performed over the past few months, and understand the value of our 'Summon Companion' spell in dungeon crawling, we will be left on our own - soloing mobs and playing Gems while we meditate.<P>And, unfortunately, the focus will never be taken from our pets, as you suggest, because our class is viewed by the game designers as THE pet class.  Without our pets, and with the lameness of the things we summon, we're merely weak wizards.  What would you rather have on a raid that you're organizing?  A Mage without a pet?  Or a Wizard?  (I'm referring to mid to high-level encounters here.)<P>Many people play mages because they want to solo.  Many of us solo because most of the time we have no other alternative.
