<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Hail Friends, just thought I'd throw in my 2cp<P>First off, Mages do have uses in high level encounters, but only in some conditions.  Mod rods can be useful to speed up a wipeout in the planes, but that's only if you don't have a click-stick up there, which now, is considered roughing it.  Pets can be useful in groups adding alot of extra melee damage, and earth pets really can soak up a pounding.  <P>What VI fails to realize, is that a mage is absolutley pet dependant.  All other classes have some way other than gate to get the heck out of Dodge.  Necros can snare/fear/FD/Shadowstep/root.  Enchanters have Mez/Memblur/root/fear/charm.  Shamans get Root/Sow.  Druids get root/snare/animal based fear&charm.  Magicians have none of those.  If our pet goes in a battle, that's it...you better hope you can outrun the mob to the nearest zone, 'cause you're dead.  In solo play no pet=dead mage.  Not with chanters necros or shamans.  Necros get more get out of jail free cards than is probably fair.  <P>Don't get me wrong.  I don't want to be a necro...I like my Direct Damage, and I LOVE my pet.  I just don't think it's fair to base a players life and death on a barely controllable NPC.  Sure, mage pets are "the best" but that doesn't warrant them being our entire chance at surviving an encounter.  Even at the high levels it's hard/impossible to channel through a mobs melee.  <P>  As far as the new spells go, letting druids outnuke mages is an absolute joke.  Not to mention the fact that Seeking Flame of Seukor is NOT DD, it's a bolt, that is all but unusable in an epic encounter.  <P>  I really can't say much about low/mid levels, as our nuke/pet combo is usually more than enough to solo a single spawn, but if two mobs join the party...again, pretty much a dead mage.  Mages should get SOMETHING that incapacitates a mob for a few precious seconds.  <P>  I can go on and on how the mage class gets totally jipped.  Look at the Jaundiced bone bracer...Rightclickable DD for a Shaman....raise your hand if you're a mage with some right-clickable direct damage item...Didn't think so.  Gloves of flame from BW don't count...20pt AoE doesn't quite do it for me.  All our PoG and quest armor right clicks are for Pet buffs/damageshields/and the ever useless reclaim energy.  <P>Some of the SoL spells will be nice, like the anti-summoning sheild.  How many of us will see level 60?  Not too many.  Veil of the Elements is a joke, Unless it's targetable.  We deserved improved invis when all the other casters got it.  Rod of Transvergence would be nice if it was like a summonable item with a right-click, instant cast gate, but it will probably be a mod rod with 3-5 charges for 5-10 times the mana cost.  Instead of giving us little trinkets to hand out to newbies, why not something we'll actually use.  How about a summonable item with 3 charges of Blaze at level 51?  Or a right clickable instant cast movement enhancer for a short amount of time?  Maybe, something melee classes will use, like a right-clickable gate stone, or weapons with procs that are pet only...like snare.  <P>   Mages also get no sort of boosted mana regeneration, singling us out as the only caster class without it after SoL hits the shelves.  Clarity/Lichform/manaskin/Form of the Great Bear/Form of the Howler/and the new cleric SoL spell all add mana ticks.  One shot mod rods do NOT count as mana regen as we lose both mana and health in the conversion.  <P>   Another thing, lest me not forget, is the fact that mages can haste thier pet, but so can every other class that gets them, however, Shamans and Enchanters can slow the mobs speed, which DRAMATICALLY increases their pets life expectancy.  Post 50 they can slow a mob almost 70%.   I can't even imagine my pets lasting 70% less damage than they do now.  God, I might be able to Solo a mob only burning through 60% of my mana.<P>  Don't get me wrong...I love my mage, he's a total blast to play, but with the lack of enchancemt to our class post 50, soloing is not an option.  The downtime because of no mana regen, cost of chancasting pets and the inherent danger of the tactic with no fallback is just not viable to pick up a shred of xp, wait 15 minutes, and risk it all again.  So, Alas, I'll sit in Karnors again, begging for a group with some core classes so we can get experiance at a moderate rate, and continue on my quest to be a CoH bitz for some of the "not quite so uber" raids.<P>Allaa K`Zamm<BR>[54 Elementalist] (Dark Elf) &lt;Norrath Travel Bureau&gt; zone: noexp<P>--------------------<P>[54 Elementalist] Allaa (Dark Elf)  zone: noexp
</FONT>
