I completely agree that post 50 the class is broken and ineffectual.  Poor pathing and high aggro make pets bad choices in many 50+ dungeons.  Sure we can summon pets as strong as 49th level, however low level characters npc or not draw aggro from greater distances than higher level ones.  Couple this with the fact that VI decided to increase the rating of pets on npc hate lists and you have a whole mess of trouble.<P>And as any mage will tell you our spells are balanced around the ideal that we have a pet to compensate for longer casting times, higher mana costs and higher resist rates.  <P>But this is preaching to the choir.  We all know things are wrong and I thought up spells but didn't think of any pet fixes.  Does anyone have any inventive suggestions?<P>One idea another mage came up with was a few new pet commands for added control.<P>  /pet assist &lt;target&gt;<BR>  /pet do not attack &lt;target&gt;<P>Also why verant feels we need to hear about the people that are baking, and fletching in our groups but recently decided that our pets special attacks should be a part of combat text is beyond me.  <IMG SRC="confused.gif" border="0">
