<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Well I have no more or less influence on the game designers than anyone else here I think. But I've since fleshed out the spell ideas a bit more for game balance from the responses I've gotten.  What do you think of the spells with these changes.<P>Summon Mask of the Magician level 24- Summon No Rent Mask AC 1 Face or main slot, with random Racial Illusion. - The general consenus seems to be that illusions are the domain of enchanters and even though uncontrolled and strictly racial this spell is out of character for the class<P>Summon Trickster's Boots level 29- Summon No Rent boots AC 4 feet or main slots that have two charges of Shadow Step-<BR>Casting time 4 seconds, casting time when clicked for effect 2.1 seconds mana 50.  Also suggested that this spell be research or quest only.  Bring some of those elements back into the game rather than random dropping.<P>Summon Cloak of Cloak of Shadows level 34- Summon No Rent Cloak AC 5 back and main slots that has two charges of Invisibility-<BR>casting time 5 seconds castimg time when clicked for effect 5 seconds mana 80  Again a spell that should be researched or quested for.<P>Enhance Summoning level 39- a 400 hp heal to pet. Keeping in mind that as casters and not healers none of these "pet heal" spells should be particularly mana or time conservative. However it is without a doubt something our class is lacking.- Casting time 5 seconds mana 250 recast 6 seconds<P>Summon Mana Shard level 44- Summons a No Drop mana shard, effect: Harvest. Casting time 4 seconds. Casting time when clicked for effect, 10 seconds. Mana Cost 10. Recast time 10 minutes. Mana gained 171-301.-  Again many players feel that the "Harvest Effect" is the domain of wizards only and that this spell would not be in game balance.<P>Revitalize Summoning level 49- Heal over time to pet 600 hp.<BR>Casting time 6 seconds Mana 300 recast time 7 seconds<P>Walnan's Familiar Augment level 49- An improved version of the level 29 SoL spell.<P>Bristlebane's Bag of Tricks level 53- Summons a glowing back pack with a Ring of Flight, a Modulating Rod, Cloak of Shadows and Trickster's Boots - It's been a subject of debate over the presence of Modulatin Rod as one of the items summoned here.  The main focus appears to be over, if it is included among the summoned items then the mana cost should be signifcantly higher than the cost of Gift of Xev or Bristlebane's Bundle which are the closest in-game spells to this.  Casting time 4 seconds mana 400<P>Revitalize Summoning level 57- an 800 hit point heal over time to pet.  Casting time 7 seconds mana 400 recast time 8 seconds<P>Cyclone level 57- an AoE radiating from the magician 2.5 second casting that deals 225 and carries a 4 to 8 second stun. -  To prevent the Magician from being able to chain stun mobs a lengthy re-cast time has been suggested.  Also it's been suggested that this spell have a poor mana efficiency rate.  To compensate I feel the damage should be increased.  Personally as this spell is pre-described as area effect rather than single target and since the damage is light I feel it's a balanced spell.  Area spells must be chosen carefully for each situation.  In delicate raid operations AoE will usually cause wipe outs and enchanter deaths.  New specs. Area Effect spell casting time 2.5 seconds mana 225 damage 500 recast time 15 seconds maximum stun time of effected targets 8 seconds<P>Raging Elements level 57- Summons a random elemental equal to the level 39 Lesser Conjuration series of pets. Casting time 2.5 seconds.  Mana 200<P>Lava Pit level 58- A fire based Root 600 hp DoT Casting time 7 seconds maximum root time 30 seconds mana 300 <P>Shield of the Arch Magi level 59- A greater Shield Spell with HP , AC, Magic Resist like the previous ones in this series with the added ability of Fire and Cold resists added to make it more Magician Specific. Much like Shield of the Magi and Elemental Armor combined and improved. I think this spell should be shared by wizards. Necromancers should have increased poison and disease resist added to theirs rather than fire and cold, while the Enchanter version has more magic resist than the others but lesser resist bonuses to fire, cold, poison and disease added on it.  Casting time 8 seconds mana 300<P>Summon Fires of Solusek Ro level 59- Summons a No Rent, No Drop fire crystal effect Manaskin. Mana cost 400. casting time when cast and clicked for effect 5 seconds. Max duration 2 hours.Spell Component 1 peridot. Self Protective skin 400. Self Mana regen (1).  A surprising number of outside players said the mana regen factor on this spell was too conservative. Especially since the hit point value of the buff was decreased and the level needed to cast it so high.  It was suggested that the regen value be increased from (1) tick to perhaps (3) or (4) giving it proper value as a 59th level spell.<P>Burnout V level 60- I'd like to see a substantial improvement over Burnout IV. Which is a good spell but feels like an intermediary to something better to come.<BR>Providing the pet with %80 haste , 100 strength and 50 ac.  Also providing each pet with a "rage of the elements" proc. A magic based damage attack providing 100 points of damage when cast.  This in addition to the pet's standard abilities.<P>Failure of Magi'Kot level 60- Summons a random elemental slightly more powerful than a greater voceration of it's randomed type. However it can not be controlled by the magician. It will act and react like an enchanter animation. Casting time 5 seconds.  Mana 600 double mana cost for summoning such a powerful attacker in half the standard time. <P>Strength of Brell Serillis level 60- 1000 heal over time to pet.  Casting time 8 seconds mana 500 recast time 8 seconds<P>Touch of the Elemental Master level 60- Magic based direct damage spell. Mana 400. Casting time 6 seconds. Recast time 6 seconds. Yield 1225 damage. <P>Why so much effort?  The only way changes happen are if the people care, if the people speak out.  Raise a fuss!  Throw some heck!  Write some e-mails!  Send some links.  Tell anyone that cares about the magician class and this game what you've read and have them do the same.  It starts with wanting to make difference.  And because of what I see and don't see in Shadows of Luclin and the magician class post 50, I want to make a difference.
</FONT>
